NOTES
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

- The HighGrid core library (src/) is original work licensed under MIT, except
  for the selected MDI icon path data listed in entry #4.

- sparklinePlugin (src/plugins/sparklinePlugin.js) renders mini charts using
  native browser SVG APIs only. No external charting library is required or
  bundled.

- echartsPlugin (src/plugins/echartsPlugin.js) optionally lazy-loads Apache
  ECharts (entry #3 above) via dynamic import. ECharts is Apache-2.0, which
  is compatible with MIT for use in open-source and commercial projects.

- formulaPlugin (src/plugins/formulaPlugin.js) optionally lazy-loads
  hot-formula-parser (entry #2 above) via dynamic import, with a CDN fallback.
  Without it, the core FormulaManager still works with its built-in =SUM / =AVG
  support — the plugin only unlocks the full Excel-style function set.

- MIT and Apache-2.0 are both permissive licenses. You can use MIT-licensed
  HighGrid together with Apache-2.0 ECharts without license conflicts.
  However, when distributing a compiled application that includes ECharts,
  you must retain the Apache-2.0 copyright notice.
